Package: pairedcountbrms
Title: Skellam, Discrete-Difference, and Joint Bivariate-Count brms
    Custom Families
Version: 0.6.0
Authors@R: person("Adam N. H.", "Smith", , "anhsmith@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides custom brms families for comparing two paired count
    sources, via two complementary approaches. First, families that model the
    difference directly: the symmetric and asymmetric Skellam distributions
    (the distribution of the difference of two Poisson random variables), and
    discrete Laplace and discrete normal distributions discretised via CDF
    differencing, each available with location fixed at zero (testing whether
    two sources agree on average) or with a free location parameter
    (quantifying systematic disagreement), all sampled on a common SD-scale
    spread parameter and supporting truncation via brms's resp_trunc().
    Second, joint bivariate-count families built by trivariate reduction -- a
    bivariate Poisson (bipois) and its overdispersed bivariate
    Negative-Binomial sibling (binegbin) -- that model a matched pair of
    counts jointly, capturing their correlation, marginal overdispersion, and
    difference together rather than the difference alone, plus a
    censoring-aware extension (binegbin_joint) that admits rows on which one
    of the two counts is unobserved via its integrated-out marginal. Intended
    for modelling set-level agreement between paired count sources.
